commit.message: Added a link to the skill on the Alexa Store in README.md
Updating README.md to reflect recent commit with issue of negative chips. Also adjusted priority of some existing tasks.
Polishing up some of the prompts/responses and addressing the issue with negative chips.
Minor updates to README.md.
Updated TODO list in README.md to add more print statements for logging purposes.
Updated TODO list in README.md with the existing issue of decimal values for the chip reverting the game state to the difficulty menu.
Added third difficulty mode to README.md
Updated README.md with previous commit regarding plural/singular forms of chip(s).
Fixed plural/singular of chip(s) in speech output.
New utterance for example on store page.
Removed example code at bottom of file. Fixed phrasing issues of voice feedback. Fixed edge cases and bugs with invalid words or numbers being inputted as the difficulty.
Added new task to TODO in README.md
Modified utterances to reflect examples on skill storepage.
New utterance for difficulty.
Updated README.md regarding temporary workaround to skip the instructions.
Updated TODO list in README.md, bugfixes on PlayerWin(), and improved sentence pauses when Alexa picks up chips.
Bug fix with syntax error.
Lowered maximum possible length of a hard game.
More bug fixes for string and int comparisons when checking win conditions.
Removed comment at the top referring to example schema and slots. Bug fixes for string and int comparisons. No longer spams Alexa app with cards for every dialog interaction.
Added StopIntent and CancelIntent to intent.json (these two are default AMAZON intents).
Added new utterances for LaunchRequest of difficulty
Bugfixes on the applicationID, number of chips initialization, and speech_output text spacing.
Implemented win conditions for PlayerWin() and PlayerLose(). Foundation of win logic has been implemented.
Updated README.md to reflect the suggestion of user playing again (instead of prompt). Updated utterances to include those involving the keyword "take"
Planning approach on how to handle win conditions and edge case of the final turn before the win.
Added task to the TODO (option of playing new game, rather than just suggesting it and then quitting after game over).

Restructured code to flow from top to bottom in a more sequential order. The setup of the board has been implemented, and the core game loop is roughly programmed. The win condition and edge cases for the final turn have not been written yet. There has been NO testing so far.
Modified utterances to correspond with the new GetNumber intent.

Modified README.md to depict uncertainty on instructions being read if difficulty is specified as launch_intent. Also added the GetNumber intent for the user to use to respond with the number of chips to take off the table.
